column5: nice bow brian !!! that creek looks mint ...

The rain is just what the creeks needed here. Nice running waters and pools had some color to them. My set up was a 5.5 fenwick light action rod,4 pound test line,2 BB shots and a Powerbait 3 inch natural worm.  Rewarded with a nice natural rainbow. I was targeting Browns.  Team one will not like it,but I left my tape in my hoody,at home.   Im guessing 18 inches.Sign is 4x6 . Nice red line and cheeks.  Real nice fish.Chunky to. Released to play another day.      Hitting it again Sunday morning.
Nice looking spot and fish!
Nice little Football.
I wanted to play more,but got called into work.  Davey,you good for Sunday?
Thats a BEAUT!!
Another nice fish!!!!, I won't know till later,I'll have to let you know B.
Well done B, nice little fatty there.  Rough estimates are good enough, especially with the sign for comparison
There was, and still is, a brown under that wood on Wednesday.  Nice fish.
Purdy rainbow Brian, good on you for letting her go!
My walk will be way down Sunday Rob. You care to join?
Nice fish Brian...good luck in the Tourney(heck...your gonna need it  )

I have no need or want, for fresh water fish any more. I can get my needs ,like I have said,from the local munger.,  I was so pleased with this catch. Been many, many years,since I fished this creek. Nice return surprise.
Nice fish, but the setting is spectacular!
you're having a great spring there MF - all you need now is some brookies to make it SPECKtacular ? Nice fish.
Doesn't count.. you spelled Ontario wrong!  Good to see you've found a new lease on life...
Thanks Wayne.Back to what I enjoyed,many years ago. Im in my happy place.
Do I need to repeat myself here   Guess I do   Guess I have to again     Nice Bow B   Congrats on your PB TJunkie
If that is the same creek that I think it is, try a mepps #1 rainbow.  The browns always seem to hit it there!
Nice One Brian!!! Sign is what, 8 1/2 x 11, so that would be about a 28 incher

I hear ya Mike. I got several this morning,wee ones. I walked and walked. Some real beautiful water.So many log jams to fish (and lose tackle   )  After today,Im thinking I want to try fly fishing. There was some kind of hatch today,and I seen many fish surfase.I tried keeping the spin bait on the surface,but no takers.  One spot,I sat and just watched the water. The action was crazy. Wish I had a fly.

The hatch you saw was May Flies B... Last Friday I saw lots of them get eaten    while I was trowing hardware    Trout were gorging themselves jumping clear out of the water   Wish I had flies in my tackle box
Very nice trout Brian. Congrats !
Very nice trout Brian. Congrats !
Awesome Brian
Nice fish.....will trade perch for a trout/salmon for my smoker....
